# Clean Code & Performance (FleetFlow)

## Architecture — single source of truth

| Layer | Location | Responsibility |
|-------|----------|----------------|
| Types & constants | `taxiTypes.ts` | Shapes, labels, defaults |
| Business logic | `utils/*.ts` | Calculations, filters, permissions, persistence |
| API / DB | `server/` | Auth, validation, SQL, routes |
| UI | `components/` | Render, local UI state, wire utils — **no duplicated math** |

Before writing new logic, search `utils/` and `server/` for an existing function. Extend it instead of copying.

## DRY — do not duplicate

- **Forbidden**: same formula, filter, or API call in two components.
- **Extract** when used twice: pure helpers → `utils/`; shared UI → small components (`AppModal`, `ConfirmDialog` pattern).
- **Config once**: labels and keys from `taxiTypes.ts` / `EXPENSE_FIELD_LABELS` — never hardcode parallel string maps in JSX.
- **API**: use `utils/taxiApi.ts`, `authApi.ts`, `taxiFleetPersistence.ts` — one fetch/save path per resource.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — dashboard math in component
const net = revenue - Object.values(expenses).reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0);

// ✅ GOOD
const totals = computeDashboard(entries, settings);
```

## File size & components

- Keep components focused. If a file exceeds ~400 lines, extract tabs, tables, or modals into `components/`.
- Prefer **functional components** + hooks (`useFitPageSize`, `useLockBodyScroll`) over class components.
- Colocate small helpers only when used in one file; move to `utils/` when reused.

## React performance

- **Memoize expensive work**: `useMemo` for `computeDashboard`, filtered/sorted lists, chart data.
- **Stable callbacks**: `useCallback` for handlers passed to memoized children or large lists.
- **Avoid render churn**: do not create new object/array literals in JSX props every render when child re-renders matter.
- **Lists**: stable `key` (id, not index); paginate (`paginateEntries`, `TRACKING_PAGE_SIZE`) — never render thousands of rows.
- **Lazy load**: heavy routes/screens via `React.lazy` (see `App.tsx`).
- **Images**: use `vehicleImage` utils; avoid huge base64 in state — compress before save.
- **Saves**: use `scheduleSaveVehicleState` debouncing — do not sync full state on every keystroke.

## TypeScript quality

- Export types from the module that owns the domain (`UserSession` in `taxiAuth.ts`).
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes; use unions for finite states (`'pending' | 'approved'`).
- No `any` for new code. Use `unknown` + narrow, or generics.
- Return typed results from API helpers (`LoginApiResult`, `FleetFetchResult`).

## Functions & naming

- **Pure functions** in `utils/`: no side effects; easy to test in `scripts/test-*.mjs`.
- Names: verbs for actions (`loadFleet`, `filterEntries`), nouns for data (`DashboardTotals`).
- Early returns over deep nesting. Max ~3 levels of indentation in new code.

## Error handling & boundaries

- API: validate input, return clear HTTP status + message; log server-side, never leak stack to client.
- UI: user-visible errors in Arabic/English per existing patterns; do not fail silently.
- Async: `try/catch` on fetch; handle `null` / empty fleet without crashing.

## Imports & dependencies

- Group: React → third-party → `../utils` → `../components` → types.
- Do not add npm packages unless necessary; prefer existing stack (Vite, Express, pg, recharts).
- No dead code, commented-out blocks, or `console.log` left in production paths.

## Refactor checklist (before finishing)

- [ ] No duplicated logic — shared code lives in `utils/` or `server/`
- [ ] Types accurate; no new `any`
- [ ] Lists paginated or virtualized where large
- [ ] Saves debounced; no redundant API calls
- [ ] Matches naming and patterns in neighboring files
- [ ] Tests updated (`test-cases-maintenance.mdc`)
